# Code Conventions
- Validate at the boundary before domain logic.
- Use early returns for auth/ownership checks.
- Keep responsibilities focused (no mixed transport/domain concerns).

# Security Rules
- Never commit secrets (`.env*`, tokens, keys).
- Never trust client input; always validate/sanitize.
- Restrict destructive actions to authenticated ownership/authorization.
- Keep upload handling constrained by validation (mime/size/type).

# Documentation Update Rules

> **MANDATORY: Any code change MUST include documentation updates in the same changeset. No exceptions.**

When code changes, update affected docs in the same change set.

1. Identify impacted surfaces: API, auth flow, data model, tooling, security rules, standards, flows, etc.
2. Update the proper file (doc, prompt, skill, or rule) — see mapping below.
3. Keep wording concise and executable (agent-first, no narrative).
4. If a rule change is driven by user feedback, ask approval before changing standards.

## Change → Doc Mapping

| What changed | Files to update |
|---|---|
| API endpoint added/changed/removed | `README.md` (endpoint table) · `docs/specific-api-model.yml` · `docs/specific-tech-backend-doc.mdc` (API Surface section) |
| DB schema / migration added/changed | `docs/specific-data-model.md` · `README.md` (tables section) |
| Auth flow changed | `docs/specific-tech-backend-doc.mdc` · `docs/specific-tech-frontend-doc.mdc` |
| Frontend route / page / UX behavior changed | `docs/business-doc.mdc` |
| Frontend stack / tooling / convention changed | `docs/specific-tech-frontend-doc.mdc` |
| Backend stack / tooling / convention changed | `docs/specific-tech-backend-doc.mdc` |
| Dev scripts / setup / deploy changed | `README.md` · `docs/specific-tech-doc.mdc` · `backend/DEPLOY.md` (if deploy-related) |
| Security rule changed | `docs/tech-doc.mdc` (Security Rules section) |
| New skill or OpenSpec change added | `ai-specs/skills/` or `openspec/` — update or create relevant artifact |
| General coding standard changed | `docs/tech-doc.mdc` |

